ire block since it pre-existed and wasn’t our change. \\n\\nI realize the method call to getDeclaredMethod requires the EncodingUtil to be initialized and invokes its static method accordingly. This means it ensures that the class is initialized before calling it. I’m wondering if there's an issue with using the `$` sign in the method name.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring method accessibility and reflection**\\n\\nI’m considering the method's synthetic package-private nature under Java 17 modules. Since it’s in the unnamed module, there shouldn't be module issues. Good to confirm that no tests have run yet, but it seems the user might still have problems with direct reflection tests like BasicScheme. I wonder if dynamic reports are excluding reflection from tests or if the native image metadata agent isn't instrumenting these methods properly. \\n\\nIf the `class$` method isn't reachable in the native image, it could cause issues, especially if the method metadata isn’t present.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection and metadata**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the JVM records reflection and whether the native image metadata includes methods. Could the dynamic-access report come from a JVM agent before the metadata is finalized? I need to check that. It seems the test class might not be included, which is untracked but should be. I wonder if I could explicitly use Class.forName through the public API. It's already direct and final, but I need to remember not to run it.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined `EncodingUtilTest` to force execution of the uncovered synthetic helper call site directly.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/EncodingUtilTest.java`\n\nAdded:\n- `compilerGeneratedClassLookupReturnsEncodingUtilClass()`\n  - obtains the compiler-generated `class$(String)` method on `EncodingUtil`\n  - invokes it with `org.apache.co